<br>
If there are not too many obviously specific topic threads on the first page of GENERAL, I leave them there until they age to the second page of GENERAL.  Then I move them to the appropriate forum so someone can find them.<br>
<br>
If there are too many obviously specific threads, especially if they are basic questions that have been answered in the specific forum, I get out my weed whacker and start editting.  I usually lock the thread, with a post explaining why, and then when they age past the first page, unlock and move them where they belong.<br>
<br>
Sometimes when there are a lot of specific threads in GENERAL, I get a little over enthusiastic.<br>
<br>
